        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 25 at 7:00PM CDT by NWS Birmingham AL</headline>
        <description>At 659 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Winterboro, or 7 miles southwest of Talladega, moving southeast at 10
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Talladega, Alpine, Winterboro, and Chandler Springs.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
